This paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for detecting unauthorized IoT devices on organizational networks. The primary focus is on the security implications of IoT devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of a supervised machine learning algorithm (Random Forest) for classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of network traffic data for feature extraction and classification suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning for security purposes, which could also place it under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE).
